The paper focuses on link prediction in graphs, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in computer science. The use of community structure and node features suggests that the paper could belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks). The use of discriminative models and the evaluation protocol suggest that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the use of surprise values and link densities suggests that the paper could belong to cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing).
